🏗️ Phase 1 – Server Preparation

Update the server:

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

Install essential packages:

sudo apt install git curl wget vim htop tree unzip zip net-tools fail2ban ufw -y

Verify:

git --version
curl --version
👥 Phase 2 – User Management

Create a DevOps user:

sudo adduser devops

Grant sudo access:

sudo usermod -aG sudo devops

Verify:

groups devops
🔐 Phase 3 – SSH Hardening

Edit SSH configuration:

sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config

Update:

PermitRootLogin no
PasswordAuthentication no
PubkeyAuthentication yes
MaxAuthTries 3

Restart SSH:

sudo systemctl restart ssh
🔥 Phase 4 – Firewall

Enable firewall:

sudo ufw enable

Allow required ports:

sudo ufw allow 22
sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw allow 443

Check status:

sudo ufw status verbose
🛡️ Phase 5 – Fail2Ban

Start service:

sudo systemctl enable fail2ban
sudo systemctl start fail2ban

Verify:

sudo fail2ban-client status
💾 Phase 6 – Backup Script

Create backup.sh

#!/bin/bash

mkdir -p backups

tar -czf backups/system-backup-$(date +%F).tar.gz /etc /home

Run:

chmod +x backup.sh
./backup.sh
📊 Phase 7 – Health Check Script

Create health-check.sh

#!/bin/bash

mkdir -p reports

REPORT="reports/health-report-$(date +%F).txt"

echo "===== HEALTH REPORT =====" > "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Hostname:" >> "$REPORT"
hostname >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Uptime:" >> "$REPORT"
uptime >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "CPU Load:" >> "$REPORT"
top -bn1 | head -10 >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Memory:" >> "$REPORT"
free -h >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Disk:" >> "$REPORT"
df -h >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Network:" >> "$REPORT"
ip addr >> "$REPORT"

echo "" >> "$REPORT"

echo "Running Services:" >> "$REPORT"
systemctl --type=service --state=running >> "$REPORT"

echo "Report Generated Successfully"
