🔥 Production Scenario

Problem: A newly provisioned Ubuntu server must be ready for production within one hour.

Your Checklist
Update the OS.
Install required packages.
Create an administrative user.
Configure SSH key-based authentication.
Disable root login and password authentication.
Enable UFW with only ports 22, 80, and 443 open.
Install and verify Fail2Ban.
Create automated backups.
Configure hourly health reports and daily backups with cron.
Verify logs, disk usage, memory, CPU, and network connectivity.
Document all configuration changes.
🧠 Senior DevOps Challenge

Create a single script named production-server-bootstrap.sh that:

Updates the operating system.
Installs essential packages.
Creates a devops user (if it doesn't already exist).
Configures UFW.
Installs and enables Fail2Ban.
Creates backup, report, and log directories.
Installs cron jobs for backups and health checks.
Produces a final summary showing:
Hostname
IP address
Disk usage
Memory usage
UFW status
Fail2Ban status

The script should be idempotent, meaning it can be run multiple times without causing errors or duplicate configuration.

